Date: Tue, 3 Nov 2015 22:56:58 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 317/452] crypto: tcrypt - do not allocate iv on stack for
 skcipher tests
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix yet another "device driver maps memory from stack" DMA-API warning.

Signed-off-by: Horia GeantÄƒ <horia.geanta@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR6.0,
LS2085A-SDK-SOURCE-20160304-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 crypto/testmgr.c |    8 +++++++-
 1 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/crypto/testmgr.c b/crypto/testmgr.c
index f9bce3d..a348ab5 100644
--- a/crypto/testmgr.c
+++ b/crypto/testmgr.c
@@ -917,11 +917,15 @@ static int __test_skcipher(struct crypto_ablkcipher *tfm, int enc,
 	const char *e, *d;
 	struct tcrypt_result result;
 	void *data;
-	char iv[MAX_IVLEN];
+	char *iv;
 	char *xbuf[XBUFSIZE];
 	char *xoutbuf[XBUFSIZE];
 	int ret = -ENOMEM;
 
+	iv = kmalloc(MAX_IVLEN, GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!iv)
+		goto out_noiv;
+
 	if (testmgr_alloc_buf(xbuf))
 		goto out_nobuf;
 
@@ -1145,6 +1149,8 @@ out:
 out_nooutbuf:
 	testmgr_free_buf(xbuf);
 out_nobuf:
+	kfree(iv);
+out_noiv:
 	return ret;
 }
 
